OL,6,FHe told the officers he had merely
OL,7,Fwanted to "enjoy" the drone and knew
OL,8,Fthe legal altitude limit for the
OL,9,Faircraft was 400ft. He admitted it was
OL,10,F"well above the legal altitude limit".
OL,12,FCaptain Peter Delaney branded the
OL,13,Fdrone pilot "dangerous and reckless".
OL,15,FJudge Jenny Lester-Ashworth said the
OL,16,Fdefendant's "culpability is
OL,17,Fsignificantly reduced by virtue" of
OL,18,Fhis autism, and so jail was 'not
OL,19,Fnecessary'.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/9
