OL,6,F"If you do you must make sure you
OL,7,Fcheck all the requirements before you
OL,8,Fdo something like this again. This
OL,9,Foffence is viewed as serious which is
OL,10,Fwhy you are in the crown court and not
OL,11,Fthe magistrates' court.
OL,13,F"This is an offence which does cross
OL,14,Fthe custody threshold."
OL,16,FThe judge went on, however, that if
OL,17,Fthe defendant did not have special
OL,18,Fneeds in the form of autism he "would
OL,19,Fbe going to prison".
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
